HEADWORD: Rubidine
<hw>Ru"bi*dine</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A nitrogenous base homologous with pyridine,
obtained from coal tar as an oily liquid, <chform>C11H17N</chform>;
also, any one of the group od metameric compounds of which rubidine is
the type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

